{"_id":"6LGgR88WOuQ3f4bW","name":"Share Senses","permission":{"default":0,"zcRawgexeM2xX0kp":3},"type":"action","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements </strong>Your eidolon is manifested.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>You project your senses into your eidolon. When you do, you lose all sensory information from your own body but can sense through your eidolon’s body for up to 1 minute. You can Dismiss this effect.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Special </strong>Your eidolon can also use this action to project their senses into your body.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["concentrate","divination","magical"],"custom":"Summoner"},"rarity":{"value":"common"},"usage":{"value":"held-in-one-hand"},"rules":[],"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":"1"},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"skill_requirements":{"skill":"","rank":""},"skill_requirement":{"skill":{"skill":"","rank":""}}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.png"}
{"name":"Striking Spell","permission":{"default":0,"zcRawgexeM2xX0kp":3},"type":"action","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p>\n<hr>\n<p>You drastically alter a spell to combine it with a martial attack. If the next action you use is to Cast a Spell that can target one creature or object, instead of casting it as normal, you place its magic into one melee weapon you’re wielding or into your body to use with an unarmed attack.</p>\n<p>If you hit with a melee Strike using the receptacle for the spell, the spell is discharged, affecting only the target you hit. The spell still requires its normal spell attack roll or saving throw, but you don’t increase your multiple attack penalty until after attempting both the discharging Strike and the spell attack roll. If your discharging Strike was a critical success, the&nbsp;degree of success is one better than you rolled for a spell attack roll or one worse than the target rolls for a saving throw.</p>\n<p>If you don’t expend the stored spell with a Strike before the end of your next turn, it is lost and dissipates harmlessly. The same thing happens if you take the Striking Spell action again or if the weapon is used for a non-melee Strike (such as a thrown weapon Strike). A spell stored with Striking Spell can’t be discharged by anyone but the caster.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["concentrate","metamagic"],"custom":"Magus"},"rarity":{"value":"common"},"usage":{"value":"held-in-one-hand"},"rules":[],"actionType":{"value":"free"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":""},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"skill_requirements":{"skill":"","rank":""},"skill_requirement":{"skill":{"skill":"","rank":""}}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/FreeAction.png","_id":"6SjZggdmdUfVnQ5A"}
{"name":"Beast's Charge","permission":{"default":0,"zcRawgexeM2xX0kp":3},"type":"action","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your eidolon rushes forward, using their momentum to power their attack. Your eidolon Strides twice in a straight line and then Strikes, gaining a +1 circumstance bonus to the attack roll as long as they moved at least 20 feet.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":[],"custom":"Eidolon"},"rarity":{"value":"common"},"usage":{"value":"held-in-one-hand"},"rules":[],"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":"2"},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"skill_requirements":{"skill":"","rank":""},"skill_requirement":{"skill":{"skill":"","rank":""}}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.png","_id":"NEKOeBrMuNWXy4HD"}
{"name":"Draconic Frenzy","permission":{"default":0,"zcRawgexeM2xX0kp":3},"type":"action","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your eidolon makes one Strike with their primary unarmed attack and two Strikes with their secondary unarmed attacks (in any order). If any of these attacks is a critical hit against a foe, the eidolon instantly recovers the use of their Breath Weapon.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":[],"custom":"Eidolon"},"rarity":{"value":"common"},"usage":{"value":"held-in-one-hand"},"rules":[],"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":"2"},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"skill_requirements":{"skill":"","rank":""},"skill_requirement":{"skill":{"skill":"","rank":""}}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.png","_id":"OHORbEiijyRDIggb"}
{"name":"Wyrm's Breath","permission":{"default":0,"zcRawgexeM2xX0kp":3},"type":"action","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Frequency </strong>once every 10 minutes</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Your eidolon concentrates the power of the mightiest wyrms to make their Breath Weapon more spectacular. If your eidolon’s next action is to use Breath Weapon, both the damage and area of the Breath Weapon are doubled.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["concentrate","metamagic"],"custom":"Eidolon"},"rarity":{"value":"common"},"usage":{"value":"held-in-one-hand"},"rules":[],"actionType":{"value":"free"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":""},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"skill_requirements":{"skill":"","rank":""},"skill_requirement":{"skill":{"skill":"","rank":""}}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/FreeAction.png","_id":"PL8BB7JGuxRYZ9Rt"}
{"_id":"PQm7J6dJrFpfsx7w","name":"Act Together","permission":{"default":0,"zcRawgexeM2xX0kp":3},"type":"action","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Frequency </strong>once per round</p>\n<hr>\n<p>You and your eidolon each perform a single action. You choose which order the actions are taken, and you and your eidolon can each take a different action.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":[],"custom":"Summoner, Tandem"},"rarity":{"value":"common"},"usage":{"value":"held-in-one-hand"},"rules":[],"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":""},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"skill_requirements":{"skill":"","rank":""},"skill_requirement":{"skill":{"skill":"","rank":""}}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.png"}
{"name":"Primal Roar","permission":{"default":0,"zcRawgexeM2xX0kp":3},"type":"action","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your eidolon unleashes a primal roar, or another terrifying noise that fits your eidolon’s form. Your eidolon attempts Intimidate checks to Demoralize each foe that can hear the roar within 30 feet.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["auditory"],"custom":"Eidolon"},"rarity":{"value":"common"},"usage":{"value":"held-in-one-hand"},"rules":[],"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":"2"},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"skill_requirements":{"skill":"","rank":""},"skill_requirement":{"skill":{"skill":"","rank":""}}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.png","_id":"YxrFSyBmLdOOaScl"}
{"name":"Dutiful Strike","permission":{"default":0,"zcRawgexeM2xX0kp":3},"type":"action","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>A foe within 15 feet of you hits you with a Strike and deals damage to you.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements </strong>Your eidolon is adjacent to you.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Your eidolon instinctively flashes with ectoplasmic energy, allowing them to make a melee attack against a foe who dares to harm you. Your eidolon makes a Strike with a melee unarmed attack against the triggering foe, even if that foe isn&rsquo;t within your eidolon&rsquo;s reach.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["occult","transmutation"],"custom":"Eidolon"},"rarity":{"value":"common"},"usage":{"value":"held-in-one-hand"},"rules":[],"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":""},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"skill_requirements":{"skill":"","rank":""},"skill_requirement":{"skill":{"skill":"","rank":""}}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Reaction.png","_id":"Zv9OtppzJ8NTKkeh"}
{"name":"Whirlwind Maul","permission":{"default":0,"zcRawgexeM2xX0kp":3},"type":"action","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your eidolon lashes out in all directions. Your eidolon makes a Strike with a melee unarmed attack against up to four enemies within reach. They can choose different unarmed attacks for each enemy. Each attack counts toward your multiple attack penalty, but don’t increase your penalty until your eidolon has made all their attacks.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":[],"custom":"Eidolon"},"rarity":{"value":"common"},"usage":{"value":"held-in-one-hand"},"rules":[],"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":"2"},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"skill_requirements":{"skill":"","rank":""},"skill_requirement":{"skill":{"skill":"","rank":""}}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.png","_id":"c1DEf9NV5VL4ofrD"}
{"_id":"jftPmR0mqItaKf9r","name":"Manifest Eidolon","permission":{"default":0,"zcRawgexeM2xX0kp":3},"type":"action","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your eidolon appears in an adjacent open space. If your eidolon was already manifested, choose whether to unmanifest them or teleport them to an adjacent open space.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Special</strong> This action has the trait matching your eidolon’s tradition (arcane, divine, occult, or primal).</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["concentrate","conjuration","magical","manipulate","teleportation"],"custom":"Summoner"},"rarity":{"value":"common"},"usage":{"value":"held-in-one-hand"},"rules":[],"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":"3"},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"skill_requirements":{"skill":"","rank":""},"skill_requirement":{"skill":{"skill":"","rank":""}}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/ThreeActions.png"}
{"name":"Breath Weapon","permission":{"default":0,"zcRawgexeM2xX0kp":3},"type":"action","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your eidolon exhales a powerful blast of energy corresponding to their type. Your eidolon deals 1d6 damage in the area you chose when your eidolon gained Breath Weapon with a basic Reflex save against your spell DC. This damage has the type you chose when the eidolon gained this ability. Your eidolon can’t use their Breath Weapon again for the next 1d4 rounds.</p>\n<p>At 3rd level and every 2 levels thereafter, the damage increases by 1d6.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["arcane","evocation"],"custom":"Eidolon"},"rarity":{"value":"common"},"usage":{"value":"held-in-one-hand"},"rules":[],"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"weapon":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":"2"},"requirements":{"value":""},"trigger":{"value":""},"skill_requirements":{"skill":"","rank":""},"skill_requirement":{"skill":{"skill":"","rank":""}}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.png","_id":"t2jusewgZ4dSaJdf"}
